longBusinessSummary: ImmunityBio, Inc., a clinical-stage immunotherapy company, develops cell and immune therapies to treat cancers and infectious diseases. The company develops Anktiva (N-803), an IL-15 superagonist and PD-L1 that activates natural killer and T effector cells in combination with chemo and trodelvy to treat cancers, such as merkel cell carcinoma, advanced pancreatic cancer, and advanced triple negative breast cancer; and an albumin-linked formulation of doxorubicin (Aldoxorubicin) to treat breast cancer, hodgkin lymphoma, SCLC, sarcoma, and glioblastoma. It also develops a memory T-cell cancer vaccine to deliver tumor-associated antigens and neoepitopes; and a human adenovirus 5 COVID-19 vaccine. The company was founded in 2014 and is based in San Diego, California.
